**who —** THE QUARK — a techne sphere — the art

**what —** A proton is not solid — it is three quarks held in a roaring field of gluons, the carriers of the strong force. Quarks carry 'colour charge,' and the force between them is so strange that they can never be isolated: pull two apart and the binding field stretches like a band, storing energy until it snaps into a fresh quark-pair. This is real physics, here drawn as ink.

**where —** the art — a generative rendering of a scale  Framework inputs: the scale; the ink; the geometry; the honesty  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** A proton is not solid — it is three quarks held in a roaring field of gluons, the carriers of the strong force. Quarks carry 'colour charge,' and the force between them is so strange that they can never be isolated: pull two apart and the binding field stretches like a band, storing energy until it snaps into a fresh quark-pair. This is real physics, here drawn as ink.

**how —** Original generative art informed by the public record.

**◌ the mythos —** A proton is not solid — it is three quarks held in a roaring field of gluons, the carriers of the strong force. Quarks carry 'colour charge,' and the force between them is so strange that they can never be isolated: pull two apart and the binding field stretches like a band, storing energy until it snaps into a fresh quark-pair. This is real physics, here drawn as ink. a view that cannot be photographed, only drawn

